22/01/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- It was announced on Wednesday (21 January) that the government has reached a compromise with the IMF on cutting budget expenses to offset new increases in the minimum wage and pensions. 
The agreement allowed the completion of the 7th review of Turkey's performance under its stand-by agreement with the Fund, which covers 2002-2004. 
Out of a total of $19.1 billion in financing, $2.5 billion remains to be disbursed. 
Completion of the 7th review will trigger the disbursement of about $507m. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV, IMF - 21/01/04)
